{"author":{"id":"1949ffc23f11a8cb4f8c42a45c9ad241b49570df9a18687489e9ea78d87c54a3"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772048142,"nonce":"CjjHVnI3BbuWUsp+MWUOs0i6QHY=","title":"Return validation losses in `TaskTrainerHistory`","message":"[Imported from GitHub #26] (created 2024-03-02T17:06:15Z)\n\nAt the end of a training run, [`TaskTrainer`](https://github.com/mlprt/feedbax/blob/98978811c362ee29987f1343b96325eddee78310/feedbax/train.py#L60) returns auxiliary information such as losses and intermediate model states in a `TaskTrainerHistory` object.\n\nThe history of the training loss is returned in the `loss` field, but the validation loss is not returned.\n\nValidation is only performed once every `log_step` trials, so a little care will need to be taken that the returned arrays are comparable with those for the training loss; it might be appropriate to return arrays that are all NaN except on the log steps. Memory should not be an issue. Usually there won't be more than 5 loss terms or so, and (conservatively) less than 100,000 iterations. That's about 2 MB of float32.","files":null}]}